    "an LLM fine-tuned on Alpaca+ functions as the encoder, compressing the original prompt into a smaller set of KV values.",
    "These KV values then serve as input to the decoder (the same fine-tuned LLM), which generates corresponding responses.",
    "Different from CC, GIST can compress unseen prompts without additional fine-tuning, achieving a compression ratio of up to 26x, though it is limited by the maximum compressible prompt length used in its fine-tuning dataset.",
    "Additionally, the compression tokens cannot be used with the original untuned LLM, restricting its broader applicability.",
    "AutoCompressor shares a similar architecture with GIST and can handle long-context prompt compression up to 30,720 tokens (Chevalier et al., 2023)."
